{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/moves-to/sweden-2020/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Eric Peterson","author":"Eric Peterson","baseUrl":"https://eric.pe","siteUrl":"https://eric.pe/terson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7711aa56-f775-5006-b6c2-3b57e79f69c4","excerpt":"For those not already aware, some personal news: I’ve moved to Stockholm,\nSweden. Given the new year, I wanted to briefly reflect on how I ended up here. 202…","html":"<p>For those not already aware, some personal news: I’ve moved to Stockholm,\nSweden.</p>\n<p>Given the new year, I wanted to briefly reflect on how I ended up here. 2020\nhas been a trying year for everyone. In one sense, I haven’t been impacted at\nall by everything going on in the world: I will end the year just as I began\nit, developing software in front of a computer screen from home.</p>\n<p>In another sense, 2020 was the peak of a multi-year run-up in anxiety and\nmental fatigue for me. How little my good fortune has changed compared with the\nunimaginably many misfortunes around me became an unignorable cognitive\ndissonance. I spent a lot of energy worrying about systemic problems I struggle\nto see solutions to.</p>\n<p>I believe my ideal social contract would be something like this: I want to be\nfree to focus my energy on my work, relationships, and interests. For this\nfreedom, I’d gladly contribute to a state that administers programs that reduce\nthe need for individuals like me to have to focus their energy on anything else.</p>\n<p>In practice, this is stuff like equal access to healthcare, education,\nchildcare, welfare, and time-off: things that in the US are not a given and end\nup distributed unevenly.</p>\n<p>So I find myself here, a guest of Sweden, which at least at first glance seems\nto operate under such a social contract. I’ve enjoyed learning the language,\nthe culture, and look forward to a little more of a hands-on approach to it all\nin the coming year or so, pandemic permitting.</p>\n<p>While uprooting your life and moving halfway around the world is not possible\nfor everyone, I hope that those also suffering from the mental fog of the last\nyear and beyond find time to reflect on why, and find a better allocation of\nenergy in the coming year.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Goodbye Seattle","date":"December 31, 2020","description":"Hello Stockholm","hideImage":null,"langKey":"en","isTranslated":true,"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/terson/static/11e1c247b25c1ddfe3d445bfb5c546cc/3cd17/sunset-on-seattle.jpg","srcSet":"/terson/static/11e1c247b25c1ddfe3d445bfb5c546cc/f463d/sunset-on-seattle.jpg 340w,\n/terson/static/11e1c247b25c1ddfe3d445bfb5c546cc/2426e/sunset-on-seattle.jpg 680w,\n/terson/static/11e1c247b25c1ddfe3d445bfb5c546cc/3cd17/sunset-on-seattle.jpg 1360w,\n/terson/static/11e1c247b25c1ddfe3d445bfb5c546cc/4fb49/sunset-on-seattle.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px"}}}}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2008-11-27T22:15:00-08:00","title":"Asleep at the Wheel"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/asleep-at-the-wheel/"}},"previous":null,"next":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-06-19T16:00:00-08:00","title":"Not Here, Not Home"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/not-here-not-home/"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-06-19T16:00:00-08:00","title":"Not Here, Not Home"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/not-here-not-home/"}},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2008-11-27T22:15:00-08:00","title":"Asleep at the Wheel"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/asleep-at-the-wheel/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-09-02T17:10:26-07:00","title":"tangled; we weave"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/tangled-we-weave/"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-09-02T17:10:26-07:00","title":"tangled; we weave"},"fields":{"slug":"/records/tangled-we-weave/"}},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"date":"2009-06-19T16:00:00-08:00","title":"Not H